Heat the oil in a saucepan over a medium-low heat. Add the onion and garlic and sauté gently without allowing to colour.Add the tomatoes, season with salt and pepper and simmer for 10 minutes, until it becomes a thick sauce.Meanwhile, bring a pan of salted water to the boil and cook the pasta for 8–10 minutes, until al dente.While the pasta is cooking, add the capers, chilli and black olives to the tomato sauce.Once cooked, drain the pasta and toss through the sauce. Stir through the anchovies and parsley. Check the seasoning and serve immediately.